HEADWORD: Concretionary
<hw>Con*cre"tion*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining
to, or formed by, concretion or aggregation; producing or containing
concretions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concretive</ent>⟦br⟧
